The paper deals with handwriting recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for this task falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of a probabilistic character error rate, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR).
